# signoz_notification_channel (Resource)

Creates and manages notification channel resources in SigNoz.

## Example Usage

```hcl
resource "signoz_notification_channel" "slack_ops" {
  name = "slack-ops-alerts"

  slack_configs {
    api_url       = var.slack_webhook_url
    channel       = "#ops-alerts"
    send_resolved = true
    title         = "[{{ .Status | toUpper }}] {{ .CommonLabels.alertname }}"
    text          = "{{ range .Alerts }}*{{ .Labels.severity }}*: {{ .Annotations.description }}\n{{ end }}"
  }
}
```

## Schema

### Required

- `name` (String) Name of the notification channel. Changing this forces recreation.

### Optional

- `id` (String) Unique ID for the notification channel. If provided during creation, the provider will adopt the existing channel.
- `slack_configs` (Block List) Slack notification configuration. (see below for nested schema)
- `webhook_configs` (Block List) Webhook notification configuration. (see below for nested schema)

### Read-Only

- `type` (String) Type of the notification channel (derived from config block).
- `created_at` (String) Creation time of the notification channel.
- `updated_at` (String) Last update time of the notification channel.

### Nested Schema for `slack_configs`

Required:

- `api_url` (String, Sensitive) Slack incoming webhook URL.

Optional:

- `channel` (String) Slack channel to post to (e.g. #ops-alerts).
- `send_resolved` (Boolean) Whether to send a notification when the alert resolves. Default: `true`.
- `title` (String) Go template for the Slack message title.
- `text` (String) Go template for the Slack message body.
- `icon_emoji` (String) Slack icon emoji for the bot.
- `username` (String) Slack username for the bot.

### Nested Schema for `webhook_configs`

Required:

- `url` (String) Webhook endpoint URL.

Optional:

- `send_resolved` (Boolean) Whether to send a notification when the alert resolves. Default: `true`.

## Import

Notification channels can be imported using their ID:

```shell
terraform import signoz_notification_channel.example <channel-id>
```
